                            <comment id="12368394" author="djd" created="Thu, 2 Mar 2006 08:32:23 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;Chris Newell wrote: (on derby-user)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; I seem to have resolved my own issue as I was preparing a message to&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; this list seeking help (thanks!). Having spent more hours than I care to&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; admit trying to figure this out, and having seen another user in the&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; list archive that had a similar problem with no solution provided, I&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; thought that I&apos;d post this with hopes of helping someone else that made&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; the same stupid mistake.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;snip class cast exception &amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; The solution was:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; -------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; I found that I had put a copy of derby.jar in both $TOMCAT/common/lib as&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; well as $TOMCAT/webapps/&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;my app&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;/WEB-INF/lib. I removed the one under&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; webapps and suddenly, as if by magic, I could count the rows in my&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; table.... And the world seems like a nicer place.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12368592" author="djd" created="Fri, 3 Mar 2006 05:09:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed and confirm with test case&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
